- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of algorithms for automated analysis.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with cardinality constraints for interpreted sets.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper establishes complexity results for the fragment of Presburger arithmetic.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with formal languages and decision procedures for checking invariants and model-checking.
